data.chText: 抓住；攫取
data.enText: to take or hold sb/sth with your hand suddenly, firmly or roughly

data.chText: 她抓住孩子的手就跑。
data.enText: She grabbed the child's hand and ran.

data.chText: 他抓住我不松手。
data.enText: He grabbed hold of me and wouldn't let go.

data.chText: 吉姆从盘子里抓了一块蛋糕。
data.enText: Jim grabbed a cake from the plate.

data.chText: 别抢——多着呢，人人都有。
data.enText: Don't grab─there's plenty for everyone.

data.chText: （试图）抓住，夺得
data.enText: to try to take hold of sth

data.chText: 她抓树枝，可没抓着，就跌倒了。
data.enText: She grabbed at the branch, missed and fell.

data.chText: 凯特拼命去夺抢劫者的枪。
data.enText: Kate grabbed for the robber's gun.

data.chText: 利用，抓住（机会）
data.enText: to take advantage of an opportunity to do or have sth

data.chText: 这是我的大好机会，我紧紧抓住。
data.enText: This was my big chance and I grabbed it with both hands.

data.chText: 他会随便找个借口来逃避洗碗。
data.enText: He'll grab at any excuse to avoid doing the dishes.

data.chText: （尤指匆忙地）取，拿，吃，喝
data.enText: to have or take sth quickly, especially because you are in a hurry

data.chText: 咱们赶快吃个三明治就走吧。
data.enText: Let's grab a sandwich before we go.

data.chText: 我在飞机上抓紧时间睡了两个钟头。
data.enText: I managed to grab a couple of hours' sleep on the plane.

data.chText: 赶紧找个座位吧，我不会耽误你太多工夫。
data.enText: Grab a seat , I won't keep you a moment.

data.chText: （尤指自私、贪婪地）捞取，赚取，抢占
data.enText: to take sth for yourself, especially in a selfish or greedy way

data.chText: 我们到达时，所有的好位子都给人占了。
data.enText: By the time we arrived, someone had grabbed all the good seats.

data.chText: 引人注意；吸引
data.enText: to get sb's attention

data.chText: 我来看能不能引起服务员的注意，让她拿账单来。
data.enText: I'll see if I can grab the waitress and get the bill.

data.chText: 格拉斯哥的毒品问题成了今晚报纸的头条新闻。
data.enText: Glasgow's drugs problem has grabbed the headlines tonight (= been published as an important story in the newspapers).
how does…grab you?

data.chText: 你对…有兴趣吗；你喜欢…吗；你认为…如何
data.enText: used to ask sb whether they are interested in sth or in doing sth

data.chText: 你认为去趟罗马这个主意如何？
data.enText: How does the idea of a trip to Rome grab you?

data.chText: 猛然的抓取；突然的抢夺
data.enText: a sudden attempt to take or hold sb/sth

data.chText: 他突然去抢她的手提包。
data.enText: He made a grab for her bag.

data.chText: 抓取（或截取、采集）的图像
data.enText: a picture taken from a television or video film, stored as an image on a computer

data.chText: 从星期三的节目中抓取的荧屏图像
data.enText: a screen grab from Wednesday's programme

data.chText: 抓具；抓斗
data.enText: a piece of equipment which lifts and holds goods, for example the equipment that hangs from a crane
up for grabs

data.chText: 提供的；可供争夺的
data.enText: available for anyone who is interested

data.chText: 在我们的比赛中有25 000英镑奖金供人争夺！
data.enText: There are £25 000 worth of prizes up for grabs in our competition!

means: 抓取(或截取、采集)的图像

ex.chText: 小偷抢了她的钱包逃跑了。
ex.enText: The thief snatched her purse and ran away.

ex.chText: 老鹰抓住一只鸽子飞走了。
ex.enText: The hawk snatched a pigeon and flew away.

ex.chText: 她走过去，好像要把信从他那里夺过来。
ex.enText: She walked over as if to snatch the letter from him.

synonyms.bx: 指突然地抢、夺、抓，强调动作迅速或具有暴力性质。

ex.chText: 那孩子紧紧抓住她的胳膊不放。
ex.enText: The child clutched her by the arm.

ex.chText: 他跳起来试图抓住那树枝，但没有成功。
ex.enText: He jumped up to clutch at the branch, but missed.

ex.chText: 抓救命稻草是无济于事的。
ex.enText: It is useless to clutch at straws.

synonyms.bx: 指因不想失去而紧紧地抓住某物，或因害怕、疼痛、危险等而突然抓住某人或某物。

ex.chText: 小偷猛地一把夺过她的钱包逃跑了。
ex.enText: The thief suddenly grabbed/snatched the purse from her and escaped.
Don't grab/snatch, there's plenty for everyone.
Quick, grab hold of that rope.

synonyms.bx: 指突然抓住某人或某物，强调动作粗野，作此义解时常可与snatch 换用；有时也指紧紧抓住某人或某物。

ex.chText: 抓住我的手，我把你拉过墙来。
ex.enText: Grasp my hand and I'll pull you over the wall.

synonyms.bx: 指紧紧地、牢牢地抓住某物。

ex.chText: 那个可怜的孩子紧紧地抓着母亲的手。
ex.enText: The poor child gripped his mother's hand.

ex.chText: 她使劲抓住栏杆，尽量不往下看。
ex.enText: She gripped the rail and tried not to look down.

synonyms.bx: 指用尽全力死死抓住某物，与 grasp 同义，但语气更强。

ex.chText: 他从书架上取了一本书。
ex.enText: He took a book from the shelf.
Someone took my cup by mistake.

ex.chText: 营房被攻占之后遭到了毁坏。
ex.enText: The camp was taken and destroyed.

synonyms.bx: 最普通用词，指用手拿、取、抓或控制某物，不带任何感情色彩。

tr: the act of catching an object with the hands
example: Mays made the catch with his back to the plate
he made a grab for the ball before it landed
Martin's snatch at the bridle failed and the horse raced away
the infielder's snap and throw was a single motion

tr: a mechanical device for gripping an object
capture the attention or imagination of

example: She grabbed the child's hand and ran out of the room

tr: take hold of so as to seize or restrain or stop the motion of
make a grasping or snatching motion with the hand
example: The passenger grabbed for the oxygen mask

tr: get hold of or seize quickly and easily
example: I snapped up all the good buys during the garage sale

value.def: If you grab something, you take it or pick it up suddenly and roughly.

example.ex: I managed to grab her hand...
I grabbed him by the neck.

value.def: If you grab at something, you try to grab it.

example.ex: He was clumsily trying to grab at Alfred's arms.
example.tran: 他笨手笨脚地想抓住艾尔弗雷德的手臂。

example.ex: I made a grab for the knife...
Mr Penrose made a grab at his collar.
example.tran: 彭罗斯先生试图揪住他的衣领。

value.def: If you grab someone who is walking past, you succeed in getting their attention.

example.tran: 玛丽·安，叫那位侍者过来。

value.def: If you grab someone's attention, you do something in order to make them notice you.

example.ex: I jumped on the wall to grab the attention of the crowd.
example.tran: 为了吸引那群人的注意，我纵身跃上墙头。

value.def: If you grab something such as food, drink, or sleep, you manage to get some quickly.
If you grab something such as a chance or opportunity, or grab at it, you take advantage of it eagerly.

example.ex: She grabbed the chance of a job interview...
example.tran: 她抓住了一次求职面试的机会。

example.ex: He grabbed at the opportunity to buy his castle.
example.tran: 他抓住机会买下了他的城堡。

value.def: A grab for something such as power or fame is an attempt to gain it.

example.tran: 对个人权力的巧取豪夺

value.def: If something is up for grabs, it is available to anyone who is interested.

example.ex: The famous Ritz hotel is up for grabs for £100m.
example.tran: 著名的里兹饭店开价1亿英镑供各方竞购。

trans: 随便吃点东西；随便吃几口；吃点东西
